==================================================================\
To submit the code in Git\
git status (will return the list of modified files, new file, deleted files)\
git add <file name> (This will add the files for commit operation)\
git commit -m <"Commit message"> (This will commit the changes)\
git push origin HEAD:refs/for/master (This will push the changes to master branch)\
==================================================================\
For Amend\
git status\
git add <file name>\
git commit --amend (change the commit message if required them :wq!)\
git push origin HEAD:refs/changes/(Unique URL id)\
	Example - https://gerrit.ericsson.se/#/c/123456/ \
	git push origin HEAD:refs/changes/123456   (No Forward Slash in the command)\
==================================================================\
Git Status\
git status (This will display the current status of your local repository)\
git status -s (This will display the current status of your local repository with short information)\
git status -sb (This will display the comparison of your local and server repository with current branch and your status)\
==================================================================\
Git Add\
Add command is used to add file for commit operation.\
git add <filename> (This will add provided file for commit)\
git add -A (This will add all files - modified, deleted, newly added)\
git add . (This will only add modified and newly added files)\
git add -u (This will add modified and deleted files)\
